narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned an appreciation of the Indian culture, the value of the language and relevance to my own life. I greatly improved my Hindi skills during this semester and am very thankful for this course and department. taking Hindi was the best academic decision I have made so far.
I gained a ton of proficiency in the language and have become far more comfortable speaking the language.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: the material moved along at a very appropriate pace, I felt pushed but not behind. the professors were very helpful and available. I am surprised with my own rapid growth in the language due to this class. it is taught in such a way that the interest in the language is maintained and promoted.
The course is well structured to facilitate learning, and is also a very fun and lively environment.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes! One of the most fun classes I have taken at Yale.
